    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen a file in `lsp/` is not a valid lsp config, `vim.lsp.config[name]` will either return `nil` or raise an error, depending on whether the given file is malformed lua or simply not a `vim.lsp.Config` table.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nGiven these two files:\n\n```lua\n-- lsp/invalid.lua\nreturn true -- incorrect type\n```\n\n```lua\n-- lsp/malformed.lua\nreturn { -- no closing brace\n```\n\n`vim.lsp.config['invalid']` will return `nil`, as if the config does not exist, while `vim.lsp.config['malformed']` will raise an error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.lsp.config[existing_config_name]` should have consistent behavior if a config file exists but is not valid.\n\nI believe that in both cases, an error should be raised. `vim.lsp.config[name]` should only return `nil` without an error if the config truly does not exist.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+2040-405c6c9bb",
